style everything in the directory @/src/ui (with the exception of project-components) and @/src/app/page.tsx following this guidelines:

- use a mobile first approach, using the md: functionality of tailwind
- change all the height and width definition to relative units to maintain proportions and prevent distortions on different size screen
- color theme:
    Primary Colors
      Primary Blue
      Hex: #3B9FE5
      RGB: 59, 159, 229
      Use: Logo, transparent navbar with blur, primary buttons, link, titles H1/H2
      Note: vibrant light blue for light backgrounds. not aggressive

      Light Blue
      Hex: #E8F5FC
      RGB: 232, 245, 252
      Uso: Background sections, card background, light hover states
      Note: Almost white with light blue tint, to maintains color consistency

      Pure White
      Hex: #FFFFFF
      RGB: 255, 255, 255
      Uso: Main Background, text on dark, card on colorful sections
      Note: neutral base with hight legibility

    Secondary Colors
      Teal Accent
      Hex: #1FBEB6
      RGB: 31, 190, 182
      Uso: secondary call-to-action, icons, dynamic elements, progress bar
      Note: maintains teal identity, perfect for vivid contrasts

      Sky Blue
      Hex: #7EC8E3
      RGB: 126, 200, 227
      Uso: Hover on primary buttons, card border on hover, animations
      Note: lighter version of the primary light blue for hover effects

  Text Color
  Primary Text (Dark Gray)
  Hex: #2C3E50
  RGB: 44, 62, 80
  Uso: Paragraphs

- use only tailwind
- font rules:
  - h1: opensans weight700
  - h2: poppins weight600
  - h3: poppins weight600
  - h4: poppins weight600
  - body: inter weight400
  - button: inter weight600
- leave comfortable spaces between elements to give a modern look, use padding and margin accordingly
- the total width at any point should be the screen's, no horizontal scroll or less than screen width
- DO NOT touch the code; only modify the tailwind styling for each component is needed
- DO NOT change the fonts.ts file in @/src/ui
- respect hierarchy, if a part is labeled as primary give it a more important styling that makes it pop out
- use wide radius to respect the modern and comfortable feel
- ADD an animation of fade in on vertical scroll, (use normal code out of tailwind if needed) to give a modern look
- if a set of cards have the same hierarchy (ex. all the platinum sponsors or the tm cards) they HAVE TO have the same dimensions
- all the cards and sections that should be the most important have to have different background that the background to make them stand out
- DO NOT use the already existent tailwind code as a guide WITH THE EXCEPTION OF ANIMATIONS AND DISPLAY PROPERTIES (don't touch the animation and use the flex direction property as guidelines)
- every img tag should have one set between height and width (with relative units)

